# Elle — environment variables
# Copy to .env for local development

# Cloudflare Worker (required)
VITE_ELLE_WORKER_URL=https://elle-worker.sbarteau2022.workers.dev
# Shared secret the local sandbox agent presents to the worker's
# SandboxAgent Durable Object. MUST match the worker's SANDBOX_AGENT_KEY
# secret (`wrangler secret put SANDBOX_AGENT_KEY`). Generate a long random
# value yourself — never commit a real key here, this file is public.
ELLE_SANDBOX_KEY=change-me-to-a-long-random-string
# Auth is a per-user superadmin JWT obtained at runtime via the login screen
# (POST /api/elle-auth on elle-worker) — same flow as elle-dev-console.
# No service key or build-time credential is needed.

# Optional: ElevenLabs for a higher-quality voice than the OS default. Unset
# by default — falls back to the free system voice automatically, including
# per-reply on any ElevenLabs error (bad key, offline, free-tier quota used
# up). Local-use only: the key ships in the browser bundle, so only set this
# when running elle yourself, never in a build you'd hand to anyone else.
# Get a key (free tier available) at https://elevenlabs.io.
# VITE_ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=
# Voice to speak with. Default below is "Rachel", ElevenLabs' stock premade
# voice. Browse others at https://elevenlabs.io/app/voice-library.
# VITE_ELEVENLABS_VOICE_ID=21m00Tcm4TlvDq8ikWAM
# Turbo models cost about half the credits per character of the standard
# models — worth it on a free-tier quota.
# VITE_ELEVENLABS_MODEL_ID=eleven_turbo_v2_5
# Longest reply ElevenLabs will speak before that one reply falls back to the
# free system voice, so one long answer can't blow the monthly quota.
# VITE_ELEVENLABS_MAX_CHARS=500

# Sovereign duplex — the local-model half of the duplex channel. It authenticates
# with ELLE_SANDBOX_KEY above and thinks via a local Ollama; all optional
# (defaults shown). Without Ollama running the loop idles harmlessly.
# The SAME two Ollama vars also power the sovereign inference lane: when the
# sandbox agent is connected, the worker's router can run whole turns
# (engine "local" / prefer:'local' / the conductor's exploration lane) on this
# model — same tools, same loop, zero provider quota.
# ELLE_OLLAMA_URL=http://127.0.0.1:11434
# ELLE_LOCAL_MODEL must be the EXACT name `ollama list` shows. The one local
# mind is Qwen3.5-4B (multimodal) — set this only if your pulled tag differs
# from the default below.
# ELLE_LOCAL_MODEL=qwen3.5:4b
# Local embedder for the multimodal intake lane — MUST be a build of
# bge-large-en-v1.5, the exact model the worker's Workers AI embedder runs,
# so local vectors land in the same 1024-dim space as the whole corpus.
# `ollama pull bge-large` gets the official library build. A different
# embedding model here would silently corrupt semantic recall — the intake
# door on the worker rejects wrong-dimension vectors for exactly that reason.
# ELLE_EMBED_MODEL=bge-large
# ELLE_DUPLEX_INTERVAL_MS=90000
